9
00:03:03,710 --> 00:03:06,283
Look like you finally free now, boys.

10
00:03:09,132 --> 00:03:10,626
Finally free.

11
00:03:11,509 --> 00:03:13,087
Friends of yours, old-timer?

12
00:03:13,177 --> 00:03:16,131
Let's just say
we spent some time together.

13
00:03:16,472 --> 00:03:21,134
Now, why do I get the feeling when you
say 'some time,' you mean some time.

14
00:03:21,394 --> 00:03:24,181
I'd been here a good while
when they come.

15
00:03:24,689 --> 00:03:27,227
They come here, must've been 1932.

16
00:03:27,692 --> 00:03:30,148
- Man!
- Shit, that's like... Wait a minute.

17
00:03:30,528 --> 00:03:32,355
That's 65 years, son.

18
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:33,645
Shit.

19
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,316
Didn't they burn in that fire yesterday?

20
00:03:36,409 --> 00:03:39,825
Listen, man, I seen them niggers
before they put them in the box.

21
00:03:39,912 --> 00:03:42,617
And when I tell you, them niggers,
they was bacon burnt.

22
00:03:42,707 --> 00:03:44,913
It was like from the X Files, man.

23
00:03:47,837 --> 00:03:49,995
What you got in that bottle anyway?

24
00:03:50,298 --> 00:03:52,670
This is Rayford's special recipe.

25
00:03:54,510 --> 00:03:59,303
He had what we call exacting standards
when it comes to the hootch.

26
00:04:01,392 --> 00:04:02,721
- So, what were they, bootleggers?
- Something like that.

27
00:04:13,321 --> 00:04:16,275
- Hank, my man, how you doin'?
- No, not tonight, Ray.

28
00:04:16,366 --> 00:04:19,283
- Spanky's not happy with you.
- Is Spanky here?

29
00:04:19,369 --> 00:04:22,488
Find a place where they let you
in the front door.

30
00:04:23,623 --> 00:04:24,453
Wait.

31
00:04:24,540 --> 00:04:26,913
Remember I bought your girl
the alligator shoes?

32
00:04:27,001 --> 00:04:28,828
What's wrong? I came through for you!

33
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:32,704
She was wearin' pigskin when I met her.
She's in alligator now. Let me in.

34
00:04:32,799 --> 00:04:35,041
Yeah, that's how it goes, brother.

35
00:04:35,134 --> 00:04:37,507
Thank you, man. I appreciate it.

36
00:04:37,637 --> 00:04:40,175
- How does this tie look?
- Lookin' sharp, man.

37
00:04:40,264 --> 00:04:42,138
I feel lucky tonight, too.

38
00:04:55,071 --> 00:04:59,021
- Here's to your new job down at the bank.
- Thank you.

39
00:04:59,075 --> 00:05:01,862
I always knew you'd make something
of yourself.

40
00:05:03,579 --> 00:05:06,783
- With my first paycheck, I'll buy...
- What, baby?

41
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:11,624
Season tickets to the Yankees,
right on the first base line.

42
00:05:12,338 --> 00:05:13,287
What's wrong?

43
00:05:13,381 --> 00:05:16,382
I was hoping you were gonna say
an engagement ring, Claude.

44
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:19,753
- Engagement ring?
- That's what respectable folks do.

45
00:05:20,805 --> 00:05:23,759
Get a job, get married, start having babies.

46
00:05:25,143 --> 00:05:27,016
Isn't that what you want?

47
00:05:27,103 --> 00:05:30,187
I just don't see no reason
to rush into things.

48
00:05:30,273 --> 00:05:33,808
I got to clean this. I'll be right back, baby.

49
00:05:48,166 --> 00:05:51,499
- Good evening, sir.
- Can I have a towel, please?

50
00:05:51,669 --> 00:05:53,662
- Of course.
- Look at this.

51
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:57,960
Hey, there ain't no reason to get violent.
I tried to call.

52
00:05:58,593 --> 00:06:00,253
Sit your ass down.

53
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:04,967
Congratulations.
You finally got yourself a job.

54
00:06:05,224 --> 00:06:08,261
Now you can pay Mr. Riley
that 50 bucks you owe him.

55
00:06:08,561 --> 00:06:11,479
- I got a bill to pay out there.
- Lookie here.

56
00:06:11,564 --> 00:06:16,107
- $22.
- Not bad... for a start.

57
00:06:16,277 --> 00:06:20,145
That's two weeks' pay. I'm with my girl.
You gotta leave me something.

58
00:06:20,239 --> 00:06:24,533
- How about your legs?
- My legs? Those are good.

59
00:06:25,578 --> 00:06:26,989
That's good.

60
00:06:27,372 --> 00:06:29,578
I'll keep the legs.

61
00:06:32,585 --> 00:06:33,914
Excuse me.

62
00:06:35,213 --> 00:06:36,707
How'd he get in here?

63
00:06:36,798 --> 00:06:37,793
Evenin'.

64
00:06:49,978 --> 00:06:52,932
- You got any of that French shit?
- Yeah, bro.

65
00:06:54,482 --> 00:06:56,273
That's the one there.

66
00:06:57,193 --> 00:06:59,150
- Thanks, man.
- All right.

67
00:06:59,988 --> 00:07:01,980
- Do I smell French?
- That's it.

68
00:07:02,615 --> 00:07:04,987
- Here, you keep the change.
- Thank you.

69
00:07:13,584 --> 00:07:16,704
- Hey, don't I know you?
- I don't think so.

70
00:07:17,255 --> 00:07:20,873
- Yes, I know you. What is your name?
- Claude Banks.

71
00:07:21,467 --> 00:07:24,137
Claude Banks! Hey, it's me, Ray Gibson.

72
00:07:24,971 --> 00:07:27,343
We went to high school. How you doin'?

73
00:07:27,640 --> 00:07:31,140
- You went to Monroe?
- Yes! How you doing?

74
00:07:31,769 --> 00:07:35,269
You lookin' all sharp.
Good to see colored folks doin' good.

75
00:07:35,356 --> 00:07:37,265
I went to Jefferson.

76
00:07:37,358 --> 00:07:39,600
You must have another Claude Banks
in mind.

77
00:07:39,694 --> 00:07:42,399
- Excuse me.
- I'm sorry. My mistake.

78
00:07:52,874 --> 00:07:54,831
Are you wearin' that dress?

79
00:07:56,919 --> 00:07:59,042
Hey, what's goin' on?

80
00:07:59,339 --> 00:08:01,580
Is it about my tab?
Don't worry, it's covered.

81
00:08:01,674 --> 00:08:03,750
It's hot in here tonight. Hot.

82
00:08:04,927 --> 00:08:08,131
This ain't about your tab.
You got bigger problems than that.

83
00:08:08,222 --> 00:08:10,132
Hold up one second...

84
00:08:10,224 --> 00:08:13,261
You shouldn't have run numbers
on Spanky's side of Broadway.

85
00:08:13,353 --> 00:08:16,638
- I think we gotta get out of here.
- Excuse me, sir, your bill.

86
00:08:16,731 --> 00:08:20,182
The bill? Of course, the bill.

87
00:08:20,777 --> 00:08:23,980
How can I forget the bill?
Such an incredibly large bill.

88
00:08:30,411 --> 00:08:32,368
Just tell me where you want me to go.

89
00:08:32,455 --> 00:08:33,618
Get over here.

90
00:08:33,706 --> 00:08:37,870
- You took my ankle.
- All right, that's not nice.

91
00:08:38,461 --> 00:08:39,872
Yeah, right?

92
00:08:40,713 --> 00:08:42,955
What do you think they're gonna do to us?

93
00:08:43,466 --> 00:08:46,087
What'd you do, dine and ditch?

94
00:08:46,177 --> 00:08:47,920
- Over ten bucks?
- Yeah.

95
00:08:48,179 --> 00:08:50,302
- Probably just a thumb.
- Who is he?

96
00:08:51,641 --> 00:08:53,183
Friend of yours?

97
00:08:53,267 --> 00:08:55,225
I never met this man before tonight.

98
00:08:55,311 --> 00:08:58,763
He's a lowlife that hangs around
in bathrooms pickpocketing people.

99
00:09:00,275 --> 00:09:01,769
I'm a professional man.

100
00:09:01,859 --> 00:09:04,350
I got a job that starts on Monday.

101
00:09:05,029 --> 00:09:07,983
I'll pay you back with my first paycheck,
with interest.

102
00:09:08,074 --> 00:09:10,316
I won't tell you how to run your business...

103
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:13,494
...but if you cut off my fingers,
you won't get nothing.

104
00:09:13,621 --> 00:09:17,037
Working on adding machines,
I got to be whole.

105
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,533
I need these for prayin'!

106
00:09:19,836 --> 00:09:23,287
- Drop him.
- What does 'drop him' mean?

107
00:09:24,215 --> 00:09:26,255
This ain't the way you treat somebody.

108
00:09:26,342 --> 00:09:29,047
Spanky, you ain't got to do that
to that guy.

109
00:09:29,137 --> 00:09:31,841
He's a square.
He didn't know who he was fucking with.

110
00:09:33,016 --> 00:09:34,723
It's filthy down there.

111
00:09:34,809 --> 00:09:37,217
Damn, there's a rat. I hate rats.

112
00:09:37,854 --> 00:09:40,641
But you do.
What does that say about you?

113
00:09:42,025 --> 00:09:43,567
What does that say about me?

114
00:09:43,651 --> 00:09:47,483
I'm just tryin' to get by.
You remember when you started out?

115
00:09:47,572 --> 00:09:48,852
Nigger, please.

116
00:09:51,993 --> 00:09:53,617
Wait a second.

117
00:09:54,579 --> 00:09:57,496
I want you to see this. Check this out.

118
00:09:57,582 --> 00:10:01,710
- I got access to that.
- Is that some more of your bathtub brew?

119
00:10:01,836 --> 00:10:04,457
Hell, no, this come up from the Mississippi.

120
00:10:04,547 --> 00:10:07,085
I can get more. I want to go into business.

121
00:10:07,175 --> 00:10:10,259
Under present circumstances,
I think I may want a partner, OK?

122
00:10:10,345 --> 00:10:13,180
I was supposed to wear this suit
on Monday!

123
00:10:14,766 --> 00:10:17,387
If you give me the front money
and a truck...

124
00:10:17,810 --> 00:10:22,307
...I can get there in two or three days,
if somebody helps me with the driving.

125
00:10:25,652 --> 00:10:29,352
- Come on, now!
- Come on, Spank.

126
00:10:35,286 --> 00:10:37,409
I'm gonna tell you something.

127
00:10:37,705 --> 00:10:42,248
- You fuck me on this, I'll spare no expense.
- I understand.

128
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:44,418
- Do you hear me?
- I hear you.

129
00:10:45,338 --> 00:10:46,797
- You got a deal.
- All right.

130
00:10:47,090 --> 00:10:49,047
Pick a man and get outta here.

131
00:10:49,384 --> 00:10:51,625
With all due respect to you gentlemen...

132
00:10:51,719 --> 00:10:54,008
...I think I'm gonna just take the choirboy.

133
00:10:54,097 --> 00:10:55,840
You got to be crazy.

134
00:10:56,099 --> 00:10:59,799
At least pick somebody
who can watch your back.

135
00:10:59,894 --> 00:11:03,097
I want someone who won't shoot me
once the truck's full.

136
00:11:03,189 --> 00:11:05,976
- Lift him.
- Not that you'd do that.

137
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,772
- Lift him!
- You know what I mean.

138
00:11:10,697 --> 00:11:12,155
There you go.

139
00:11:12,615 --> 00:11:14,655
Sure he ain't dead?

140
00:11:21,082 --> 00:11:22,790
Sure hope you can drive.

141
00:11:27,547 --> 00:11:31,876
This rum run we're doin' is gonna really
improve my relationship with Spanky.

142
00:11:32,051 --> 00:11:36,096
Good man to have on your side.
He's got capital connections.

143
00:11:36,848 --> 00:11:39,718
I ain't got capital yet, but I will.

144
00:11:39,809 --> 00:11:41,600
Then I'll have my own place.

145
00:11:41,686 --> 00:11:44,556
Don't get me wrong, I like Spanky's.
I want my own.

146
00:11:44,647 --> 00:11:46,604
I'm gonna call my place...

147
00:11:46,691 --> 00:11:48,897
...Ray's Boom-Boom Room.

148
00:11:49,152 --> 00:11:52,686
Don't that sound like a place
where it's fun? Sound excitin'.

149
00:11:52,947 --> 00:11:55,438
Ray's Boom-Boom Room. I like that.

150
00:11:56,242 --> 00:11:59,362
Wouldn't you want to check out
a place like that?

151
00:11:59,454 --> 00:12:02,075
Hell, you'd want to.

152
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,535
The Boom-Boom Room.

153
00:12:07,211 --> 00:12:08,492
What you think?

154
00:12:11,174 --> 00:12:13,131
You ain't said nothin' since we left.

155
00:12:13,426 --> 00:12:16,131
The least you can do is give me
friendly conversation.

156
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:20,135
I don't want a friendly conversation.
I don't want to be your friend.

157
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:24,895
I just want to do this thing and get back
to New York in time to start my job.

158
00:12:24,979 --> 00:12:27,102
What the hell kind of job you got?

159
00:12:27,315 --> 00:12:31,692
If you must know,
bank teller at First Federal of Manhattan.

160
00:12:34,572 --> 00:12:35,947
What's so funny?

161
00:12:36,282 --> 00:12:38,773
I'm just laughing at myself. Excuse me.

162
00:12:38,868 --> 00:12:41,988
No, you found something very amusing.
What's so funny?

163
00:12:42,121 --> 00:12:46,119
'Bank teller' just sounds like ladies' work,
I always picture a woman doing that.

164
00:12:46,209 --> 00:12:49,494
Maybe I should dig around
in other people's pockets for money.

165
00:12:49,587 --> 00:12:51,912
It's obviously been highly successful
for you.

166
00:12:52,006 --> 00:12:54,378
You'd be surprised what you find there.

167
00:12:54,717 --> 00:12:57,552
I've never heard of a man
settin' out to be a bank teller.

168
00:12:57,637 --> 00:13:00,044
This time next year, I'll be a loan officer.

169
00:13:00,139 --> 00:13:02,677
So, I go to the bank for a loan...

170
00:13:02,767 --> 00:13:04,760
...I gotta deal with a tight-ass like you?

171
00:13:04,852 --> 00:13:07,343
- That's right.
- Well, how do I get a loan?

172
00:13:07,438 --> 00:13:09,645
- You?
- Yes, me. What's 'you'?

173
00:13:10,149 --> 00:13:11,809
I can't get no money?

174
00:13:11,901 --> 00:13:15,685
- You need collateral.
- What, you think I ain't got collateral?

175
00:13:16,572 --> 00:13:20,107
I have... Look at this. What about this?

176
00:13:21,411 --> 00:13:23,866
That thing? Who'd you steal it from?

177
00:13:23,997 --> 00:13:26,488
I ain't steal that. My daddy gave it to me.

178
00:13:26,582 --> 00:13:28,824
Who'd he steal it from?

179
00:13:29,877 --> 00:13:32,547
Watch what you say about my daddy.
My daddy's dead.

180
00:13:32,630 --> 00:13:35,335
Say what you want about me.
Don't drag my daddy into it.

181
00:13:35,425 --> 00:13:38,794
This watch is sterling silver.
It's top-shelf, top of the line.

182
00:13:38,886 --> 00:13:43,216
It's very near and dear to my heart,
so no wisecracks or I'll whup your ass.

183
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:46,888
Looks like a fake to me. Loan denied.

184
00:13:47,895 --> 00:13:50,813
Fuck you. I'll take my business elsewhere.

185
00:13:50,898 --> 00:13:54,599
And for future references, you will not
be welcome at Ray's Boom-Boom Room.

186
00:13:54,694 --> 00:13:57,730
- There's no Boom-Boom Room.
- When there is one.

187
00:13:57,822 --> 00:14:01,654
When there's one, don't come,
'cause you ain't gettin' in.

188
00:14:21,054 --> 00:14:23,627
- Smell that?
- Yeah, I smell something.

189
00:14:23,723 --> 00:14:27,768
- Smells good, right?
- I think we should go to another place.

190
00:14:28,436 --> 00:14:30,725
The ambiance ain't really very welcoming.

191
00:14:30,813 --> 00:14:35,060
Are you kiddin'? Tell me you don't want
one of these pies right here.

192
00:14:35,193 --> 00:14:37,648
Them pies look good,
but I kinda lost my appetite.

193
00:14:37,737 --> 00:14:41,070
- When I came in, my appetite left.
- Good afternoon, Billy.

194
00:14:42,283 --> 00:14:45,118
We'd like some coffee
and a couple slices of pie.

195
00:14:45,328 --> 00:14:47,486
How do you know my name is Billy?

196
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:51,707
It says it right there on your shirt.

197
00:14:52,418 --> 00:14:57,127
If you boys can read so good, how come
you missed that sign on the door?

198
00:14:59,884 --> 00:15:01,462
That sign on the door...

199
00:15:01,552 --> 00:15:04,470
Why didn't we see that sign
that say 'No Coloreds Allowed'?

200
00:15:04,555 --> 00:15:07,093
We rushed in.
We was really hungry, so we missed it.

201
00:15:07,183 --> 00:15:09,223
- We see it now, so bye.
- Look, ma'am...

202
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:11,552
...we've been traveling all day.
- Let's go.

203
00:15:11,646 --> 00:15:15,264
All we want is some coffee
and a couple slices of pie, all right?

204
00:15:15,358 --> 00:15:18,110
No. These are whites-only pies.

205
00:15:19,278 --> 00:15:23,193
- Well, do you have any Negro pies?
- Claude, come on.

206
00:15:23,825 --> 00:15:26,944
This woman ain't got the recipe to it.
Where would she get that?

207
00:15:27,036 --> 00:15:29,492
At another establishment
we can get us some pies.

208
00:15:29,580 --> 00:15:32,036
- How far to the next town?
- Thirty-five miles.

209
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:35,328
I'm not driving no 35 miles to get no pie.

210
00:15:35,962 --> 00:15:37,456
Lady! Ma'am! Okay?

211
00:15:38,506 --> 00:15:41,460
Now we want some pie. We are hungry.

212
00:15:42,427 --> 00:15:44,466
Billy, we want some pie.

213
00:15:44,595 --> 00:15:47,929
- Let me take care of this.
- Someone must die 'cause we want pie?

214
00:15:48,016 --> 00:15:50,423
Let me take care of 'em.

215
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,265
We're from New York,
my name's Ray Gibson.

216
00:15:55,273 --> 00:15:59,317
How much will it cost to turn one of them
white-only pies into nigger pie?

217
00:15:59,402 --> 00:16:02,107
How about I turn y'all into nigger pie?

218
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:04,735
- So you said about 35...
- 35 miles.

219
00:16:04,824 --> 00:16:07,991
We'll find another establishment
down the road.

220
00:16:08,411 --> 00:16:11,994
Yeah, I didn't know white folks
so serious about pie down here.

221
00:16:27,180 --> 00:16:29,849
- Hey, we're lookin' for Slim.
- You found him.

222
00:16:32,685 --> 00:16:36,469
That's it, fellas.
Thirty-six cases of Mississippi's finest.

223
00:16:38,524 --> 00:16:42,273
- Five bucks a case. That's $180.
- All right.

224
00:16:42,362 --> 00:16:44,935
- What do we got?
- Come on. Pay the man.

225
00:16:46,824 --> 00:16:49,398
That music's hot.
What goes on down there?

226
00:16:49,702 --> 00:16:52,028
That there's Natchez-Under-The-Hill.

227
00:16:52,121 --> 00:16:53,948
Colored folks welcome down there?

228
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:57,207
- Green's the only color that matters there.
- Is that right?

229
00:16:57,502 --> 00:16:59,494
They got gambling, girls.

230
00:17:01,339 --> 00:17:05,123
- You boys ought to check it out.
- Maybe we will. Nice doing business...

231
00:17:05,218 --> 00:17:07,839
Let's go have ourselves a reward,
see what's shaking.

232
00:17:07,929 --> 00:17:10,883
- Reward?
- There's people there having a good time.

233
