01:07:21,359 --> 01:07:23,482
Daddy, give me my baby back.

948
01:07:29,116 --> 01:07:32,117
What you laughin' at? You laughin' at me?

949
01:07:33,287 --> 01:07:36,205
You know who the daddy
of that chocolated baby is?

950
01:07:36,624 --> 01:07:38,000
You do?

951
01:07:38,418 --> 01:07:40,457
Well, who is it? Speak up!

952
01:07:41,587 --> 01:07:43,295
It's my baby, boss.

953
01:07:43,881 --> 01:07:46,123
He's lying. I'm the father of that baby.

954
01:07:46,217 --> 01:07:48,340
Boss, I'm that baby's daddy.

955
01:07:49,887 --> 01:07:52,129
Any fool can see that baby belongs to me.

956
01:07:52,223 --> 01:07:55,343
I wanna differ.
That little rascal belong to me.

957
01:07:55,893 --> 01:07:58,563
Proud to say, boss, I'm that baby's daddy.

958
01:07:59,063 --> 01:08:02,432
- I be the pa, boss.
- I'm the pa of that there young'un.

959
01:08:03,317 --> 01:08:04,693
I the pappy.

960
01:08:32,888 --> 01:08:34,632
That was the last we ever saw...

961
01:08:34,724 --> 01:08:37,595
...of Superintendent Abernathy
and little Mae Rose.

962
01:08:39,228 --> 01:08:41,435
To celebrate his departure...

963
01:08:41,981 --> 01:08:44,602
...Camp 8 threw ourselves a little party.

964
01:08:45,693 --> 01:08:47,567
Ray provided the moonshine...

965
01:08:47,820 --> 01:08:50,608
...and Claude managed to scare up
some girls.

966
01:08:50,990 --> 01:08:54,442
It wasn't quite the Boom-Boom Room,
but it was close enough.

967
01:08:59,374 --> 01:09:00,832
Come on, now.

968
01:09:01,709 --> 01:09:04,580
She don't mean nothin' to him.
Don't pay that no mind.

969
01:09:04,670 --> 01:09:07,078
To hell with him. It ain't that.

970
01:09:08,091 --> 01:09:11,257
What's your problem,
sittin' around lookin' all sad and shit?

971
01:09:11,344 --> 01:09:14,345
It's almost all right in here today.

972
01:09:19,685 --> 01:09:21,096
What's this?

973
01:09:26,484 --> 01:09:28,726
A release form.
You gettin' out this month.

974
01:09:28,820 --> 01:09:32,769
- What you sittin' around lookin' all sad for?
- What am I gonna do out there?

975
01:09:32,865 --> 01:09:35,238
I can't go home to my mama like this.

976
01:09:35,326 --> 01:09:39,371
You are crazy. Your mama gonna be happy
when you get home.

977
01:09:39,622 --> 01:09:41,496
But not like this, Ray.

978
01:09:42,166 --> 01:09:45,784
Hey, look. The world done changed
a lot. It's 1945, boy.

979
01:09:47,005 --> 01:09:48,796
Not for me, it ain't.

980
01:09:52,510 --> 01:09:55,083
You can't stay here. That's for damn sure.

981
01:09:55,346 --> 01:09:59,510
Anybody else in the place would give
his right arm... I know I would.

982
01:10:04,063 --> 01:10:07,563
Shit. Fuckin' release papers,
sittin' over here lookin' sad.

983
01:10:08,484 --> 01:10:10,393
I won't sit here with you lookin' sad.

984
01:10:10,486 --> 01:10:13,938
You got the best news of the day
and you're sitting here looking sad.

985
01:10:14,449 --> 01:10:16,987
You cheer up. You're goin' home.

986
01:10:17,159 --> 01:10:20,160
Hey, man, that's good news.
Come on. You're goin' home.

987
01:10:20,246 --> 01:10:22,073
You gonna smile? There you go.

988
01:10:22,165 --> 01:10:24,371
I'll see you in a minute.

989
01:10:48,358 --> 01:10:50,350
Where you goin', Biscuit?

990
01:10:53,321 --> 01:10:55,812
Where you goin'? Don't do that!

991
01:10:57,992 --> 01:11:00,234
Hold it right there!

992
01:11:03,080 --> 01:11:05,287
Man over the line!

993
01:12:05,893 --> 01:12:07,387
I got Chicago!

994
01:12:08,729 --> 01:12:11,054
- Goldmouth, I got Chicago!
- Yeah?

995
01:12:11,691 --> 01:12:13,268
Come on, fellas.

996
01:12:14,027 --> 01:12:16,565
- Where you goin'?
- Why you all dressed up?

997
01:12:21,325 --> 01:12:22,736
What's this?

998
01:12:23,327 --> 01:12:25,201
What the fuck is going on?

999
01:12:28,333 --> 01:12:30,954
Blocker! What's goin' on here?

1000
01:12:31,377 --> 01:12:33,950
The kid's gettin' out. I got him a pardon.

1001
01:12:34,255 --> 01:12:37,125
What about me and Ray?
Our names ain't on the pardon.

1002
01:12:37,217 --> 01:12:40,052
- You said you put in a good word for us.
- I did.

1003
01:12:41,137 --> 01:12:43,889
I mentioned you. I mentioned both of you.

1004
01:12:43,973 --> 01:12:46,808
But the fact is, pardons don't come cheap.

1005
01:12:47,435 --> 01:12:50,270
That kid can hit. What can you guys do?

1006
01:12:50,605 --> 01:12:54,056
We're the ones who worked with him...

1007
01:12:54,317 --> 01:12:56,938
...night and day.
- Forget it, man. Let it go.

1008
01:12:57,028 --> 01:12:59,780
I'm not gonna let it go.

1009
01:12:59,864 --> 01:13:03,447
The man said he was gonna put in
a good word. Explain yourself.

1010
01:13:03,534 --> 01:13:06,451
But the kid's gettin' out,
that's what you wanted.

1011
01:13:17,131 --> 01:13:18,791
Yeah. Of course.

1012
01:13:25,264 --> 01:13:27,554
You show them Crawfords
how to play ball.

1013
01:13:27,642 --> 01:13:29,599
Make 'em throw you strikes.

1014
01:13:34,065 --> 01:13:35,939
Go. You're a free man.

1015
01:13:42,198 --> 01:13:43,692
It's all right.

1016
01:14:11,477 --> 01:14:13,803
- Come on, son.
- We love you, boy.

1017
01:14:16,232 --> 01:14:17,726
Hit that ball, boy.

1018
01:14:18,067 --> 01:14:21,152
You hit one out the park for me.

1019
01:14:22,196 --> 01:14:25,032
Play hard, Can't Get Right!

1020
01:14:30,371 --> 01:14:32,245
We'll catch you on the radio!

1021
01:14:32,332 --> 01:14:34,324
All right. So that's that.

1022
01:14:34,709 --> 01:14:37,912
A new boy told me
they're farming that land by the swamp.

1023
01:14:38,004 --> 01:14:40,874
- He saw a crop duster flyin'...
- I'm not in the mood.

1024
01:14:40,965 --> 01:14:43,717
It's behind the barn.
It can't be that hard to fly it.

1025
01:14:43,802 --> 01:14:46,209
- Lots of people do it.
- They're called pilots.

1026
01:14:46,304 --> 01:14:49,554
I'm not in the mood
for your fucked-up plans.

1027
01:14:49,641 --> 01:14:51,763
I don't hear you comin' up with no plan!

1028
01:14:51,851 --> 01:14:54,852
My plan is on his way to Pittsburgh
right now.

1029
01:14:55,605 --> 01:14:59,104
Can't Get Right just got a pardon
signed by the governor, thanks to us.

1030
01:14:59,192 --> 01:15:01,398
But we can't do nothin' for ourselves.

1031
01:15:01,486 --> 01:15:04,190
Don't you feel a little frustrated right now?

1032
01:15:04,739 --> 01:15:08,190
- Crop duster.
- I'm not gettin' in no airplane with you.

1033
01:15:13,039 --> 01:15:16,538
I'm finally wrapping my mind
around this whole concept.

1034
01:15:16,792 --> 01:15:20,742
- What concept is that?
- They threw us in this shithole for life.

1035
01:15:20,963 --> 01:15:23,003
Don't you get it? We gonna die here.

1036
01:15:23,090 --> 01:15:26,625
We might as well head to the cemetery,
pick a plot and start digging.

1037
01:15:26,719 --> 01:15:30,218
My daddy died in a place like this
because of what you're sayin'.

1038
01:15:30,306 --> 01:15:33,342
He gave up hope and hung hisself.
I ain't goin' out like that!

1039
01:15:33,434 --> 01:15:37,597
Maybe you're foolin' yourself.
Maybe you just a chip off the old block.

1040
01:15:40,274 --> 01:15:42,516
Take that back,
or we ain't friends no more.

1041
01:15:42,610 --> 01:15:45,397
News flash. We ain't never been friends.

1042
01:15:45,530 --> 01:15:48,199
We just been stuck together for 12 years.

1043
01:15:48,283 --> 01:15:51,865
It's been nothin' but pure hell
since the moment I ran into you.

1044
01:15:51,994 --> 01:15:54,616
Every time I look at you,
I get sick to my stomach...

1045
01:15:54,706 --> 01:15:57,955
...thinkin' what my life could've been
if I never bumped into you.

1046
01:15:58,042 --> 01:16:00,450
Slow down, you might say
something you'll regret.

1047
01:16:00,545 --> 01:16:05,006
- You better quiet down, nigger.
- Only thing I regret is the day I met you.

1048
01:16:07,552 --> 01:16:09,176
- That's the way it is?
- Yeah, that's the way it is.

1049
01:16:09,345 --> 01:16:12,216
I ain't got nothin' else to say to your ass.

1050
01:16:12,306 --> 01:16:13,635
Thank you!

1051
01:16:15,643 --> 01:16:19,094
Now if you ask me,
when Can't Get Right left Camp 8...

1052
01:16:19,272 --> 01:16:21,597
